# 01 - Full Stack Expense Tracker: Setup Guide

This guide summarizes the installation and setup process for a full-stack Expense Tracker app using React (frontend), Node.js/Express (backend), and MySQL (database).

---

## âœ… Prerequisites

* Node.js and npm installed
* MySQL or XAMPP (with phpMyAdmin)
* Visual Studio Code (or your preferred code editor)

---

## ðŸ“ Project Structure

```
expense-tracker/
â”œâ”€â”€ client/         # React frontend
â””â”€â”€ server/         # Express backend
```

---

## ðŸ”§ Installation Summary

### 1. Initialize project structure

```bash
mkdir expense-tracker && cd expense-tracker
mkdir client server
```

### 2. Start Backend Server

```bash
cd server
npm init -y
npm install express cors dotenv jsonwebtoken bcryptjs mysql2 sequelize
```

### 3. Start Frontend React App

```bash
cd ../client
npx create-react-app .
npm install axios react-router-dom
```

### 4. Run Servers

* Backend: `node index.js` or `npx nodemon index.js` (port 5000)
* Frontend: `npm start` (port 3000)

### 5. MySQL/phpMyAdmin

* Open XAMPP > Start Apache and MySQL
* Go to `http://localhost/phpmyadmin`
* Create database: `expense_tracker`

You're now ready to start development!
